narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: You learn Spanish. The course is a continuation of L1, so L2 just finishes covering many of the concepts that were taught beforehand.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Professor Len was very interactive and made her classes very interesting and engaging.  The way we learned material felt very natural with the flipped-classroom style learning. Perhaps one weakness was a shortcoming of this style, though, as we were limited in our in-class time spent on grammar specifics.

This class was a pretty high-school-esque class, so its strength are that you can build a very close relationship with your teachers and fellow classmates, but the weakness is that all the learning seems rather rudimentary.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, this class is a great way to improve your Spanish skills. There is a lot more work than expected, but you will learn a lot and become more fluent.

Yes I would definitely recommend this course to others as my class really grew together as the semester went on and it was such a fun environment to be a part of while learning so much about different cultures in spanish.
Its an intro level Spanish class. While a simple explanation, thats all the class was.
